(82, 'In-boost-for-faltering-process,-Colombia''s-Santos-wins-Nobel-Peace-Prize', 'In boost for faltering process, Colombia''s Santos wins Nobel Peace Prize', 'By Stine Jacobsen and Helen Murphy OSLO/BOGOTA (Reuters) - Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos won the 2016 Nobel Peace Prize on Friday for his efforts to end a 52-year-old war with Marxist rebels, a surprise choice and a show of support after Colombians rejected a peace accord last Sunday. The Norwegian Nobel Committee said Santos had brought one of the longest civil wars in modern history significantly closer to a peaceful solution, but there was still a danger the peace process could collapse. The award excluded FARC guerrilla leader Rodrigo Londono, better known by his nom de guerre Timochenko, who signed the peace accord with Santos in Cartagena on Sept. 26.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:45 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/colombian-president-santos-wins-nobel-peace-prize-091024080.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/kMdBpFfZ8jBipTyGvTZeAA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T115739Z_1_LYNXNPEC960T5_RTROPTP_2_NOBEL-PRIZE-PEACE.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(83, 'Merkel-appeals-to-Russia-to-end-''atrocious''-situation-in-Syria', 'Merkel appeals to Russia to end', 'German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Friday appealed to Russia to end what she called the &quot;atrocious&quot; violence in Aleppo, Syria, saying Moscow had a lot of influence on the Syrian government. Merkel said there was no basis in international law for the bombing of hospitals, and Moscow should help end the escalating violence in the war-torn country. (Reporting by Andreas Rinke; Writing by Andrea Shalal; Editing by Caroline Copley)', '7 Oct 2016, 1:38 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/merkel-appeals-russia-end-atrocious-situation-syria-104114323.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/kMdBpFfZ8jBipTyGvTZeAA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T115739Z_1_LYNXNPEC960T5_RTROPTP_2_NOBEL-PRIZE-PEACE.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(84, 'Monster-Hurricane-Matthew-pummels-Florida-coast-with-wind-and-rain', 'Monster Hurricane Matthew pummels Florida coast with wind and rain', 'Hurricane Matthew unleashed torrential rains and up to 120 mile-an-hour winds as it hugged the Florida coast Friday, after a blast through the Caribbean that reportedly left more than 300 dead in Haiti. Matthew was downgraded to a Category Three storm early Friday by the National Hurricane Center, as its wind speed dropped slightly. The storm caused havoc as it hit Haiti''s southern coast on Tuesday, killing more than 300 people, according to a senator from the region, Herve Fourcand.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:36 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/us-coast-evacuated-historic-hurricane-bears-down-020011738.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4YaUSe5w9urJhxr6eq5klA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/54869d1b2159d8f7f3bcb5f3be2412a4a28ee13a.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(85, 'South-Sudan,-others-with-child-soldiers-get-US-waiver-on-aid', 'South Sudan, others with child soldiers get US waiver on aid', 'President Barack Obama has issued waivers that continue millions of dollars in U.S. military assistance for troubled South Sudan and six other nations where child soldiers have been used, disappointing advocates who say his administration hasn''t made curbing the use of children in combat a higher priority.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:28 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/obama-grants-waiver-south-sudan-others-child-soldiers-102108415.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/iNAAJ9r6PhM84ZV1ZF1Z6A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/5108614b8d154cf187dceee5334ba240.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(86, 'Russia-considers-military-bases-in-Vietnam-and-Cuba:-agencies', 'Russia considers military bases in Vietnam and Cuba: agencies', 'Russia is considering plans to restore military bases in Vietnam and Cuba that had served as pivots of Soviet global military power during the Cold War, Russian news agencies quoted Russian Deputy Defence Minister Nikolai Pankov as saying on Friday. "We are dealing with this issue," the agencies quoted Pankov as saying in Russia''s parliament. Russia lowered its flag at the Lourdes signals intelligence base in Cuba and the deepwater Cam Rahn naval base in Vietnam in the early 2000s as part of a drawing down of Russia''s military presence around the world after the demise of the Soviet Union.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:27 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/russias-military-mulls-restoring-bases-vietnam-cuba-agencies-082604466.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/iNAAJ9r6PhM84ZV1ZF1Z6A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/5108614b8d154cf187dceee5334ba240.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(87, 'Cardinals-look-to-build-off-33-21-win-over-49ers', 'Cardinals look to build off 33-21 win over 49ers', 'After stumbling at the start of the season, the Arizona Cardinals hope a road win without their starting quarterback is just what they need to get their season back on track. After a fourth straight loss ...', '7 Oct 2016, 1:26 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/cardinals-look-build-off-33-21-win-over-063419681--spt.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4jXtXqiSK_aKDFDL3pa7uA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://globalfinance.zenfs.com/images/US_AHTTP_AP_NEWSBRIEFS/c32a7b5293a74784b37660bc0cae2be3_original.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(88, 'Sterling-slide-fuels-risk-off-on-U.S.-payrolls-day', 'Sterling slide fuels risk-off on U.S. payrolls day', 'Sterling recouped some losses after plunging almost 10 percent on Friday, as growing fears of a "hard" exit by Britain from the European Union sent a shiver through world stocks markets before U.S. jobs data. The impact of sterling''s slide on other asset classes was relatively muted, though caution prevailed. U.S. stock futures were down 0.3 percent before U.S. payrolls data, which could put pressure on the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:23 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/fat-finger-error-seen-sterling-slumps-asian-shares-004654070--finance.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/fs.eN99o31SQoEXb8L9eRQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T113155Z_1006950001_LYNXNPEC960RD_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-GLOBAL-MARKETS.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(89, 'Sunni-force-pleads-for-Iraqi-government-help-as-Mosul-fight-looms', 'Sunni force pleads for Iraqi government help as Mosul fight looms', 'By Michael Georgy and Babak Dehghanpisheh BASHIQA, Iraq (Reuters) - Abu Mahmoud, part of a 2,500-man predominantly Sunni Arab force pulled together to launch an offensive against Islamic State in the Iraqi city of Mosul, has heard from relatives the group has been threatening to behead anyone who speaks of "liberation". "The most important thing we need is weapons and government support," said Abu Mahmoud, 42, who like others interviewed at a training camp in Bashiqa in northern Iraq, declined to give his full name for fear of reprisals. Abu Mahmoud, who covers his face so that Islamic State militants don''t target his family, hopes he and other men in the National Mobilisation force will capture Mosul and rescue its residents in an operation expected to start within weeks.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:20 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/sunni-force-pleads-iraqi-government-help-mosul-fight-104722186.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Ugu6XtL2lYN6lXHwK_a3nw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T104722Z_1_LYNXNPEC960NE_RTROPTP_2_MIDEAST-CRISIS-MOSUL-SUNNIS.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(90, 'Backpage.com-raided,-CEO-arrested-for-sex-trafficking', 'Backpage.com raided, CEO arrested for sex-trafficking', 'State agents raided the Dallas offices of adult classified ad portal Backpage.com and arrested Chief Executive Officer Carl Ferrer following allegations that adult and child sex-trafficking victims were forced into prostitution through escort ads posted on the site.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:18 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/backpage-com-raided-ceo-arrested-052541017.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/KbsYruGdNjY_V26r4Ege9Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cHhvZmY9NTA7cHlvZmY9MDtxPTc1O3c9MTMw/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/1a28d0e5163f4b1298996b8bbb943cb3.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(91, 'Bradley-Wiggins-under-pressure-in-''drugs-probe''', 'Bradley Wiggins under pressure in ''drugs probe''', 'Bradley Wiggins is facing fresh questions about his medical history after Britain''s Daily Mail reported he was at the centre of an inquiry by United Kingdom Anti-Doping. The Mail said UKAD wanted to question him and his Team Sky bosses over a medical package delivered to the British outfit ahead of the 2011 Tour de France. A UKAD statement issued late Thursday said: "UK Anti-Doping is investigating an allegation of wrongdoing within cycling.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:15 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/bradley-wiggins-under-pressure-drugs-probe-091705468--oly.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/sudnyIphL6cFFMmMsalJCg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/fe0db520f5ddb8e26e59e52f900555f02ce3af3c.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(92, 'Flash-crash-rocks-British-pound-as-Hollande-warns-on-Brexit', 'Flash crash rocks British pound as Hollande warns on Brexit', 'Sterling suffered a dizzying &quot;flash crash&quot; against the euro and dollar on Friday in a computer-generated sell-off, sending Brexit shockwaves across markets after France warned of perils ahead for Britain.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:14 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/pound-plunges-6-1-31-low-against-dollar-004100985.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/e6218LQdbM5zX0cN.365Jw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/Part-DV-DV480781-1-1-0.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(93, 'Hurricane-Matthew-batters-Florida-as-Haiti-death-toll-rises', 'Hurricane Matthew batters Florida as Haiti death toll rises', 'By Scott Malone and Gabriel Stargardter ORLANDO, Fla./MIAMI (Reuters) - The first major hurricane threatening a direct hit on the United States in more than 10 years lashed Florida on Friday with heavy rains and winds after killing at least 339 people in Haiti on its destructive march north through the Caribbean. Hurricane Matthew packed gusts of 100 miles per hour (160 kph) as it tracked north-northwest along Florida''s east coast, the National Hurricane Center said in an advisory. The storm''s eye was 25 miles (40 km) east of Cape Canaveral, home to the nation&rsquo;s chief space launch site.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:05 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/deadly-hurricane-matthew-closes-florida-002853786.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/knzhWzquotjQ6A0Fm.xcPg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-06T223855Z_1_LYNXNPEC951K4_RTROPTP_2_STORM-MATTHEW-USA.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(94, 'Finland,-US-to-deepen-military-ties-through-pact', 'Finland, US to deepen military ties through pact', 'Finland and the United States have signed a bilateral defense cooperation pact pledging closer military collaboration at the time when the Nordic country is increasingly concerned over Russia''s activities in the Baltic Sea region.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:05 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/finland-us-deepen-military-ties-pact-110538402.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/knzhWzquotjQ6A0Fm.xcPg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-06T223855Z_1_LYNXNPEC951K4_RTROPTP_2_STORM-MATTHEW-USA.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(95, '&quot;Flash-crash&quot;-decimates-sterling', '&quot;Flash crash&quot; decimates sterling', 'By Anirban Nag LONDON (Reuters) - Sterling lost a tenth of its value in minutes on Friday, in what traders said was a "flash crash" driven by computer-initiated sell orders that left the pound at a fresh 31-year-low and heading for its worst week since January 2009. The pound has been under pressure for most of this week as anxiety grows that Britain will opt for a "hard" exit from the European Union. The drop in Asia came after French President Francois Hollande said the EU needed to remain firm with Britain, after it appeared Prime Minister Theresa May had opted for a tougher exit from Europe.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:05 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/sterling-shaky-diving-31-low-hard-brexit-fears-072714215--finance.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/2BX5djhTosxJS_pydghr.Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T072714Z_2_LYNXNPEC9607C_RTROPTP_2_BRITAIN-EU-STERLING.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
