(120, 'Colombian-leader-Juan-Manuel-Santos-wins-Nobel-Peace-Prize', 'Colombian leader Juan Manuel Santos wins Nobel Peace Prize', 'Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos won the Nobel Peace Prize on Friday for his efforts to end a five-decade civil war that has killed more than 200,000 people &mdash; and said he received the award in the ...', '7 Oct 2016, 1:59 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/colombian-president-santos-wins-nobel-peace-prize-090645191.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/JLNBxfx1CqhGaZF1hkQ1aA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://globalfinance.zenfs.com/images/US_AHTTP_AP_NEWSBRIEFS/f813beb1bd5b48ee8227021156c228c4_original.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(121, 'Germany-steps-up-pressure-on-Russia-over-Syria,-opens-door-to-sanctions', 'Germany steps up pressure on Russia over Syria, opens door to sanctions', 'German Chancellor Angela Merkel urged Russia on Friday to use its influence with the Syrian government to end the devastating bombardment of Aleppo, as her government opened the door to possible sanctions against Russia for its role in the conflict. In some of her harshest comments to date, Merkel said there was no basis in international law for bombing hospitals and Moscow should use its influence with Syrian President Bashar al-Assad to end the bombing of civilians. &quot;Russia has a lot of influence on Assad.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:59 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/german-official-calls-sanctions-against-russia-over-syria-080349243.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/JLNBxfx1CqhGaZF1hkQ1aA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://globalfinance.zenfs.com/images/US_AHTTP_AP_NEWSBRIEFS/f813beb1bd5b48ee8227021156c228c4_original.jpg"', 'sports', '1'),
(122, 'Nobel-laureate-Tutu-celebrates-85th-birthday,-giving-thanks', 'Nobel laureate Tutu celebrates 85th birthday, giving thanks', 'Nobel laureate Desmond Tutu shed tears of gratitude on his 85th birthday on Friday in South Africa, where he presided over a cathedral Mass despite his poor health. Separately, in a newspaper column, the former archbishop said he would like to have the option of a &quot;dignified assisted death&quot; when the time comes.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:56 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/nobel-laureate-tutu-celebrates-85th-birthday-giving-thanks-114949558.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Dknk1X.qhR6I_SEuk47deg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/ee9d77fc045348cda5d4cb279d47c579.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(123, 'Multiple-fatalities-likely-in-Minnesota-helicopter-crash', 'Multiple fatalities likely in Minnesota helicopter crash', 'Several people apparently died when a helicopter burst into flames as it crashed into a field in a Twin Cities suburb, a sheriff''s official said.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:53 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/many-fatalities-likely-minnesota-helicopter-crash-110018906.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Dknk1X.qhR6I_SEuk47deg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/ee9d77fc045348cda5d4cb279d47c579.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(124, '''Keeping-Up-with-the-Kardashians''-on-hold-after-robbery', '''Keeping Up with the Kardashians'' on hold after robbery', 'The E! Network has shut down production on &quot;Keeping Up with the Kardashians&quot; since Kim Kardashian West was held up in Paris.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:49 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/keeping-kardashians-hold-robbery-114432891.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/C.xNDPKL3DVbaadaA79fGQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/9c7cd492cfbc4036b07afb80134a5dd3.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(125, 'Moroccans-go-to-the-polls-in-parliamentary-ballot', 'Moroccans go to the polls in parliamentary ballot', 'Moroccans voted on Friday in their second parliamentary election since the king devolved some powers in a constitutional reform five years ago to ease Arab Spring protests calling for change. After leading the ruling coalition since 2011, moderate Islamist Justice and Development Party (PJD) is expected to dominate the ballot over main rivals the Authenticity and Modernity Party (PAM) which critics say is close to the palace. No party openly challenges the king, who retains most executive authority.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:45 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/moroccans-polls-parliamentary-ballot-114534193.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/xtr9FRL0lkBgnAFSH4EZeA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_ZA/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T114534Z_1007970001_LYNXNPEC960RZ_RTROPTP_2_OZATP-UK-MOROCCO-ELECTION.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(126, 'In-boost-for-faltering-process,-Colombia''s-Santos-wins-Nobel-Peace-Prize', 'In boost for faltering process, Colombia', 'Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos won the 2016 Nobel Peace Prize on Friday for his efforts to end a 52-year-old war with Marxist rebels, a surprise choice and a show of support after Colombians rejected a peace accord last Sunday. The Norwegian Nobel Committee said Santos had brought one of the longest civil wars in modern history significantly closer to a peaceful solution, but there was still a danger the peace process could collapse. The award excluded FARC guerrilla leader Rodrigo Londono, better known by his nom de guerre Timochenko, who signed the peace accord with Santos in Cartagena on Sept. 26.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:45 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/colombian-president-santos-wins-nobel-peace-prize-091024080.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/kMdBpFfZ8jBipTyGvTZeAA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T115739Z_1_LYNXNPEC960T5_RTROPTP_2_NOBEL-PRIZE-PEACE.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(127, 'Merkel-appeals-to-Russia-to-end-''atrocious''-situation-in-Syria', 'Merkel appeals to Russia to end', 'German Chancellor Angela Merkel on Friday appealed to Russia to end what she called the &quot;atrocious&quot; violence in Aleppo, Syria, saying Moscow had a lot of influence on the Syrian government. Merkel said there was no basis in international law for the bombing of hospitals, and Moscow should help end the escalating violence in the war-torn country. (Reporting by Andreas Rinke; Writing by Andrea Shalal; Editing by Caroline Copley)', '7 Oct 2016, 1:38 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/merkel-appeals-russia-end-atrocious-situation-syria-104114323.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/kMdBpFfZ8jBipTyGvTZeAA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T115739Z_1_LYNXNPEC960T5_RTROPTP_2_NOBEL-PRIZE-PEACE.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(128, 'Monster-Hurricane-Matthew-pummels-Florida-coast-with-wind-and-rain', 'Monster Hurricane Matthew pummels Florida coast with wind and rain', 'Hurricane Matthew unleashed torrential rains and up to 120 mile-an-hour winds as it hugged the Florida coast Friday, after a blast through the Caribbean that reportedly left more than 300 dead in Haiti. Matthew was downgraded to a Category Three storm early Friday by the National Hurricane Center, as its wind speed dropped slightly. The storm caused havoc as it hit Haiti''s southern coast on Tuesday, killing more than 300 people, according to a senator from the region, Herve Fourcand.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:36 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/us-coast-evacuated-historic-hurricane-bears-down-020011738.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4YaUSe5w9urJhxr6eq5klA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/54869d1b2159d8f7f3bcb5f3be2412a4a28ee13a.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(129, 'South-Sudan,-others-with-child-soldiers-get-US-waiver-on-aid', 'South Sudan, others with child soldiers get US waiver on aid', 'President Barack Obama has issued waivers that continue millions of dollars in U.S. military assistance for troubled South Sudan and six other nations where child soldiers have been used, disappointing advocates who say his administration hasn''t made curbing the use of children in combat a higher priority.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:28 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/obama-grants-waiver-south-sudan-others-child-soldiers-102108415.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/iNAAJ9r6PhM84ZV1ZF1Z6A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/5108614b8d154cf187dceee5334ba240.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(130, 'Russia-considers-military-bases-in-Vietnam-and-Cuba:-agencies', 'Russia considers military bases in Vietnam and Cuba: agencies', 'Russia is considering plans to restore military bases in Vietnam and Cuba that had served as pivots of Soviet global military power during the Cold War, Russian news agencies quoted Russian Deputy Defence Minister Nikolai Pankov as saying on Friday. "We are dealing with this issue," the agencies quoted Pankov as saying in Russia''s parliament. Russia lowered its flag at the Lourdes signals intelligence base in Cuba and the deepwater Cam Rahn naval base in Vietnam in the early 2000s as part of a drawing down of Russia''s military presence around the world after the demise of the Soviet Union.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:27 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/russias-military-mulls-restoring-bases-vietnam-cuba-agencies-082604466.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/iNAAJ9r6PhM84ZV1ZF1Z6A--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/5108614b8d154cf187dceee5334ba240.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(131, 'Cardinals-look-to-build-off-33-21-win-over-49ers', 'Cardinals look to build off 33-21 win over 49ers', 'After stumbling at the start of the season, the Arizona Cardinals hope a road win without their starting quarterback is just what they need to get their season back on track. After a fourth straight loss ...', '7 Oct 2016, 1:26 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/cardinals-look-build-off-33-21-win-over-063419681--spt.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/4jXtXqiSK_aKDFDL3pa7uA--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://globalfinance.zenfs.com/images/US_AHTTP_AP_NEWSBRIEFS/c32a7b5293a74784b37660bc0cae2be3_original.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(132, 'Sterling-slide-fuels-risk-off-on-U.S.-payrolls-day', 'Sterling slide fuels risk-off on U.S. payrolls day', 'Sterling recouped some losses after plunging almost 10 percent on Friday, as growing fears of a "hard" exit by Britain from the European Union sent a shiver through world stocks markets before U.S. jobs data. The impact of sterling''s slide on other asset classes was relatively muted, though caution prevailed. U.S. stock futures were down 0.3 percent before U.S. payrolls data, which could put pressure on the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:23 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/fat-finger-error-seen-sterling-slumps-asian-shares-004654070--finance.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/fs.eN99o31SQoEXb8L9eRQ--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T113155Z_1006950001_LYNXNPEC960RD_RTROPTP_2_CBUSINESS-US-GLOBAL-MARKETS.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(133, 'Sunni-force-pleads-for-Iraqi-government-help-as-Mosul-fight-looms', 'Sunni force pleads for Iraqi government help as Mosul fight looms', 'By Michael Georgy and Babak Dehghanpisheh BASHIQA, Iraq (Reuters) - Abu Mahmoud, part of a 2,500-man predominantly Sunni Arab force pulled together to launch an offensive against Islamic State in the Iraqi city of Mosul, has heard from relatives the group has been threatening to behead anyone who speaks of "liberation". "The most important thing we need is weapons and government support," said Abu Mahmoud, 42, who like others interviewed at a training camp in Bashiqa in northern Iraq, declined to give his full name for fear of reprisals. Abu Mahmoud, who covers his face so that Islamic State militants don''t target his family, hopes he and other men in the National Mobilisation force will capture Mosul and rescue its residents in an operation expected to start within weeks.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:20 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/sunni-force-pleads-iraqi-government-help-mosul-fight-104722186.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l2.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/Ugu6XtL2lYN6lXHwK_a3nw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T104722Z_1_LYNXNPEC960NE_RTROPTP_2_MIDEAST-CRISIS-MOSUL-SUNNIS.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(134, 'Backpage.com-raided,-CEO-arrested-for-sex-trafficking', 'Backpage.com raided, CEO arrested for sex-trafficking', 'State agents raided the Dallas offices of adult classified ad portal Backpage.com and arrested Chief Executive Officer Carl Ferrer following allegations that adult and child sex-trafficking victims were forced into prostitution through escort ads posted on the site.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:18 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/backpage-com-raided-ceo-arrested-052541017.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/KbsYruGdNjY_V26r4Ege9Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cHhvZmY9NTA7cHlvZmY9MDtxPTc1O3c9MTMw/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/1a28d0e5163f4b1298996b8bbb943cb3.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(136, 'Flash-crash-rocks-British-pound-as-Hollande-warns-on-Brexit', 'Flash crash rocks British pound as Hollande warns on Brexit', 'Sterling suffered a dizzying &quot;flash crash&quot; against the euro and dollar on Friday in a computer-generated sell-off, sending Brexit shockwaves across markets after France warned of perils ahead for Britain.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:14 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/pound-plunges-6-1-31-low-against-dollar-004100985.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/e6218LQdbM5zX0cN.365Jw--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/Part-DV-DV480781-1-1-0.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(137, 'Hurricane-Matthew-batters-Florida-as-Haiti-death-toll-rises', 'Hurricane Matthew batters Florida as Haiti death toll rises', 'The first major hurricane threatening a direct hit on the United States in more than 10 years lashed Florida on Friday with heavy rains and winds after killing at least 339 people in Haiti on its destructive march north through the Caribbean. Hurricane Matthew packed gusts of 100 miles per hour (160 kph) as it tracked north-northwest along Florida''s east coast, the National Hurricane Center said in an advisory. The storm''s eye was 25 miles (40 km) east of Cape Canaveral, home to the nationâ€™s chief space launch site.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:05 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/deadly-hurricane-matthew-closes-florida-002853786.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/knzhWzquotjQ6A0Fm.xcPg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-06T223855Z_1_LYNXNPEC951K4_RTROPTP_2_STORM-MATTHEW-USA.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(138, '&quot;Flash-crash&quot;-decimates-sterling', '&quot;Flash crash&quot; decimates sterling', 'Sterling lost a tenth of its value in minutes on Friday, in what traders said was a &quot;flash crash&quot; driven by computer-initiated sell orders that left the pound at a fresh 31-year-low and heading for its worst week since January 2009. The pound has been under pressure for most of this week as anxiety grows that Britain will opt for a &quot;hard&quot; exit from the European Union. The drop in Asia came after French President Francois Hollande said the EU needed to remain firm with Britain, after it appeared Prime Minister Theresa May had opted for a tougher exit from Europe.', '7 Oct 2016, 1:05 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/sterling-shaky-diving-31-low-hard-brexit-fears-072714215--finance.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l1.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/2BX5djhTosxJS_pydghr.Q--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/Reuters/2016-10-07T072714Z_2_LYNXNPEC9607C_RTROPTP_2_BRITAIN-EU-STERLING.JPG"', 'sports', NULL),
(139, 'How-a-patient''s-''crazy''-request-for-a-new-womb-made-history', 'How a patient', 'When the young Australian cervical cancer patient learned she had to lose her womb in order to survive, she proposed something audacious to the doctor who was treating her: She asked if she could have a womb transplant, so she could one day carry her own baby.', '7 Oct 2016, 12:55 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/patients-crazy-request-womb-made-history-040458018.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/BiZkX1TlOFb6Z74YypQ_1g--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/ap_webfeeds/961ac618ce824b75809411924c5fa83b.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(140, 'Madison-Keys-beats-Petra-Kvitova-in-Olympic-rematch-at-China-Open', 'Madison Keys beats Petra Kvitova in Olympic rematch at China Open', 'It took two hours and 40 minutes, three sets and two tiebreaks for Keys to end the challenge of the double Wimbledon champion, 6-3, 6-7 (2/7), 7-6 (7/5). A double fault by Kvitova turned the first set in favour of Keys, but she pulled back in the second, pushing it to a tiebreak, which she won. There was little between the pair in the final set, but Kvitova''s 32 unforced errors to Keys'' 25 ultimately cost the Czech a semi-final place -- and ended her eight-match winning streak.', '7 Oct 2016, 12:45 pm', NULL, 'http://news.yahoo.com/madison-keys-beats-petra-kvitova-olympic-rematch-china-104503443--ten.html', '2016-10-07 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://l3.yimg.com/bt/api/res/1.2/_j35FnzKFQEJCJgBl34gTg--/YXBwaWQ9eW5ld3NfbGVnbztmaT1maWxsO2g9ODY7cT03NTt3PTEzMA--/http://media.zenfs.com/en_us/News/afp.com/3257dd1581f9d904b497957a9918016f3c9f07d4.jpg"', 'sports', '2');
INSERT INTO `articles` (`id`, `slug`, `title`, `content`, `created_time`, `source`, `link`, `ma_date`, `cont_image`, `image_link`, `category`, `counter`) VALUES
(141, 'Fuming-Pique-to-quit-Spain-squad-after-sleeve-uproar', 'Fuming Pique to quit Spain squad after sleeve uproar', '\nCriticism of the defender''s jersey alteration in the 2-0 win over Albania has prompted him to confirm his international retirement after the Russia tournament\n\nSpain defender Gerard Pique has revealed that he will retire from international football following the 2018 World Cup after growing "tired" of criticism.\nThe centre-back has long been a contentious figure in the Spain ranks due to his public backing of Catalan independence, as well as his part in perceived past squabbling between Barcelona and Real Madrid players.\nCosta and Spain still struggling\nPique also came under fire from the press during Sunday''s 2-0 win over Albania, with some claiming he had cut the regulation short-sleeved jersey in order to remove the trim on the shirts that bears the design of the Spanish flag.\nHowever, the 29-year-old produced proof after the match that he had in fact cut the sleeves of a shirt that did not have the same flag design, and he says the accusations have pushed him too far.\n"I''ve tried everything but I cannot take any more," he said in a statement released by the Royal Spanish Football Federation (RFEF).\n"Today with the sleeves is the straw that breaks the camel''s back. They''ve made it so I''ve lost the excitement of coming here, and although after Russia I''ll only be 31, I''ll leave."\nThe RFEF also communicated their support for the centre-back.\n"The Royal Spanish Football Federation wants to show their support for the Spanish international Gerard Pique regarding the controversy caused by the cutting of long sleeves of his shirt in the match played against Albania," a statement read.\n"Contrary to what was indicated by some malicious comments - that the player cut his sleeves to avoid wearing a top with the national colours - the RFEF wishes to clarify that this trimming only exists in the Adidas short-sleeve shirt, and not in the long sleeves, which is what Pique wore in the match.&nbsp;\n"This lack of trimming can be seen on the shirt of his partner, Sergio Ramos, who also worse long sleeves.\nRamos faces four weeks out\n"The player cut his sleeves with the sole purpose of playing more comfortably, like other internationals have done on many occasions.\n\n"Unfair criticism of Gerard Pique has caused him to declare that he will leave the Spanish team after the World Cup in Russia."\n', '10 Oct 2016, 12:34 am', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/722/la-liga/2016/10/09/28326942/fuming-pique-to-quit-spain-squad-after-sleeve-uproar', '2016-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-89EKCgBk8MZdE.gif"', 'sports', '1'),
(142, 'RUMOURS:-Chelsea-plan-Hazard-swap-deal-for-Bonucci', 'RUMOURS: Chelsea plan Hazard swap deal for Bonucci', 'Desperate to shore up his new defence, the Blues coach is planning a raid on his former club and will use the Belgium star as bait\r\n\r\n\r\nChelsea manager Antonio Conte is planning to use Eden Hazard as a makeweight in his efforts to bring Leonardo Bonucci to Stamford Bridge, according to theÂ Sun.Â \r\nThe defender was the cornerstone of Conte''s Juventus team that lifted three consecutive Serie A titles under his tenure before he left for Italy in 2014.Â \r\nAnd with the Blues looking far from convincing in defence, he would be prepared to dispense with the Belgium star in order to convince Juve to sell their lynchpin.Â \r\nThe Bianconeri are keen on a big cash deal plus Cesc Fabregas, but Conte believes he can save transfer funds by sending Hazard to Turin instead of the midfielder.Â ', '10 Oct 2016, 12:15 am', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/11/transfer-zone/2016/10/09/28326452/rumours-chelsea-plan-hazard-swap-deal-for-bonucci', '2016-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://u.goal.com/2230400/2230482.jpg"', 'sports', NULL),
(143, 'McClean-blasts-Ireland-critics-after-Moldova-brace', 'McClean blasts Ireland critics after Moldova brace', '\nAfter firing the Boys in Green to their second win of the international break, Sunday''s hero took aim at his side''s critics in the media\n\nJames McClean blasted Republic of Ireland''s critics after his brace secured a 3-1 World Cup qualifying win in Moldova.\nIreland opened their qualifying campaign with a hard-fought draw in Serbia before an unconvincing win at home to Georgia.\nCosta and Spain still struggling\nMcClean feels the coverage Ireland received after those matches was harsh, though, and took aim at the media following the win in Moldova that helped Martin O''Neill''s side go joint-top of Group D.\n"We got a lot of flak after the Serbia game, a lot of flak after the Georgia game, and we didn''t want a repeat," he told Sky Sports.\n"I think [it''s been] unfairly so, as well. I think the Irish press need to have a reality check that we''re not going to blow teams away.\n"We''ve always been a team that works hard, but a win''s never been enough. We''re happy to get a win and we''re happy to be on seven points."\nMcClean believes that Ireland are in a "no-win" situation when it comes to pleasing their naysayers.\nHe added: "Our fans are brilliant. They follow us home and away, these supporters, and they''re amazing.\n"But, for some reason, with the media it seems to be a no-win situation. If we play pretty football and we don''t win, we should have won. If we don''t play pretty football and we win, we need to play better football.\n\n"I''ve always been one of those people that says a win''s a win, no matter how it comes."\n', '10 Oct 2016, 12:12 am', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/468/international-football/2016/10/09/28326472/mcclean-blasts-ireland-critics-after-moldova-brace', '2016-10-10 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-89EKCgBk8MZdE.gif"', 'sports', NULL),
(144, 'Costa-and-Spain-still-struggling-to-break-down-defences', 'Costa and Spain still struggling to break down defences', '\nFor all their possession, La Roja needed another goalkeeping error to take the lead against Albania and their lack of chances remains a concern\n\nCOMMENT\nIt was a happier&nbsp;ending&nbsp;for Spain this time. After the disappointment of conceding a late leveller to Italy in Turin on Thursday night, Julen Lopetegui''s team took all three points in Albania on Sunday. But it was harder than it should have been.\n&rsquo;Messi only the fifth best striker I&rsquo;ve faced&rsquo;\nAgainst Italy, La Roja had dominated virtually throughout, but they needed an uncharacteristic howler from Gianluigi Buffon to take the lead at the Juventus Stadium and it was a similar story in this one as Spain finally went ahead following an error from Albania goalkeeper Etrit Berisha in the second half.\nPrior to that, they had been in complete control. Lopetegui fielded an innovative 3-3-3-1 system with Gerard Pique, Sergio Ramos and Nacho Monreal at the back, Koke, Sergio Busquets and Thiago Alcantara ahead of them, with Vitolo, Andres Iniesta and David Silva behind lone striker Diego Costa.\n\nIt was Costa who provided the breakthrough, yet had it not been for Berisha''s mistake, the goal may not have arrived. For all their neat play, Spain lacked the ability to create chances for the Brazil-born forward and La Roja are still struggling to break down disciplined defences.\nNothing new about that, but the Costa experiment is bringing only mixed results and doubts remain in the long term over the Chelsea striker''s suitability in Spain''s system. A player who likes to run on to the ball, he fits in better with teams that play on the counter - and that simply is not this side''s style.\nCosta &amp; Nolito strike in Spain win\nNolito came off the bench and scored the second within three minutes of his introduction, linking up well around the box, beating an Albanian defender and slotting in an angled finish. That goal was much more what Spain are about and perhaps the Manchester City forward should start in this team. Nevertheless, it was also questionable defending from an Albanian point of view.\n\n\nIt is early days for Lopetegui and the signs are good&nbsp;at this stage. The performance in Italy was positive and Spain should have won that match, while this was another valuable victory away from home that leaves La Roja on top of Group G with seven points from their three games, with 11 goals scored and only one conceded.\nFirst-ever green card awarded in Italy\n"We are satisfied with the win, the performance and the commitment of the team," Lopetegui said afterwards. "These were two difficult away matches. There is a long way to go in [World Cup] qualifying and we will have to fight match by match."\n\nThat is true. But they will also need to improve because, in the last two tournaments, Vicente del Bosque''s side ultimately failed after a&nbsp;stroll through qualifying. And Lopetegui''s job is to make Spain stronger - be it with or without Diego Costa.\n', '9 Oct 2016, 11:49 pm', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/14302/comment/2016/10/09/28324632/costa-and-spain-still-struggling-to-break-down-defences', '2016-10-09 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://images.performgroup.com/di/library/GOAL_INTERNATIONAL/2a/f8/albania-spain-graphic_2hpki2i82ytp1ue6b1yro8ckq.png?t=-1421436609"', 'sports', NULL),
(145, 'Ramos-faces-a-month-out-as-Real-Madrid-dealt-more-injury-woe', 'Ramos faces a month out as Real Madrid dealt more injury woe', '\nThe defender fell heavily in Sunday''s World Cup qualifier and his club face an anxious wait to find out the severity of the problem\n\nReal Madrid''s extensive injury list has claimed a new member as Sergio Ramos looks set to be out for up to a month with a sprained knee.&nbsp;\nThe centre-back pulled up towards the end of la Roja''s 2-0 World Cup qualifying clash against Albania, and was replaced by debutant Inigo Martinez.&nbsp;\nHe limped off the pitch without assistance, but Spain head coach Julen Lopetegui suggested after the match that he''d suffered a sprain.&nbsp;\n"Sergio Ramos'' injury seems to be a sprain, let''s hope it is nothing too serious," he told reporters after the game.&nbsp;\nIf the injury is confirmed, Ramos will join the likes of Marcelo, Casemiro and Luka Modric on the casualty list at the Santiago Bernabeu, as injuries have disrupted a strong start to the season.&nbsp;\n\nThe defender, however, appears in good spirits, and joined his team-mates in the dressing room after Sunday''s clash to celebrate the win.&nbsp;\n', '9 Oct 2016, 11:47 pm', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/722/la-liga/2016/10/09/28325812/ramos-faces-a-month-out-as-real-madrid-dealt-more-injury-woe', '2016-10-09 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-89EKCgBk8MZdE.gif"', 'sports', NULL),
(146, 'Italy-extend-incredible,-decade-old-unbeaten-streak', 'Italy extend incredible, decade-old unbeaten streak', 'Sunday''s victory over Macedonia might have been a close-run affair, but it continued their impressive run in qualification matches\r\n\r\nCiro Immobile didn''t just salvage points for Italy with his match-winning double against Macedonia on Sunday - he also extended their unbeaten streak in qualification matches.\r\nMatch Report: Macedonia 2-3 Italy\r\nItaly have now gone 53 games - 39 wins and 14 draws - without losing a World Cup or European Championship qualifier.\r\nThe last time the Azzurri suffered defeat in major tournament qualification was over a decade ago, versus France in September 2006.\r\nImmobile''s double in Skopje, which came in the last 15 minutes of the World Cup 2018 qualifier, took his tally for Italy and Lazio this season to seven goals in 10 games.\r\n\r\nGiampiero Ventura''s men now sit second in Group G with seven points after three games, behind table-toppers Spain - whom they drew earlier in the international break - on goal difference.', '9 Oct 2016, 11:22 pm', NULL, 'http://www.goal.com/en/news/14552/world-cup-2018/2016/10/09/28325382/italy-extend-incredible-decade-old-unbeaten-streak', '2016-10-09 00:00:00', NULL, 'src="http://pixel.quantserve.com/pixel/p-89EKCgBk8MZdE.gif"', 'sports', '3');
